{"type":"text","timestamp":1775863375621,"sessionID":"ses_2865226aaffes9rvCi52yAPwmp","part":{"id":"prt_d79b4980d001jWUf45RYvadgsG","messageID":"msg_d79b47f82001WsCZGbGhY2woKc","sessionID":"ses_2865226aaffes9rvCi52yAPwmp","type":"text","text":"The implementation is complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## AR-022 — CLI Publish Command Implementation\n\n### Changes Made:\n\n**1. Enhanced `PublishRuntime` (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)**\n- Added agentcube provider prerequisites check: validates that `router_url` and `workload_manager_url` are present in metadata before deploying\n- Added `wait_for_deployment_ready()` call for K8s provider with timeout handling\n- Added `timeout` parameter (default 120s) to the publish method\n- Fixed error handling to properly record deployment errors in metadata\n\n**2. Comprehensive Unit Tests (`tests/test_publish_runtime.py`)** - 19 tests total:\n- Image URL preparation (4 tests)\n- K8s publish with NodePort validation (4 tests)\n- AgentCube publish with prerequisites (2 tests)\n- Publish method flow (4 tests)\n- Deployment ready timeout handling (1 test)\n- Image preparation scenarios (4 tests)\n\n### Test Results:\nAll 19 publish_runtime tests pass. The 9 failing tests in the suite are pre-existing issues in other components (k8s_provider, status_runtime) unrelated to the CLI publish command.","time":{"start":1775863375619,"end":1775863375619}}}
